The paper deals with information transmission over a channel with additive Gaussian noise and the use of feedback to improve decoding error exponent. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of feedback for improving performance in communication networks, which could fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of feedback also involves the study of control systems, which could fall under the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of feedback for improving performance in multimedia communication, which could fall under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical analysis of the achievable decoding error exponent, which could fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
